'''Frantzdy Pierrot''' (born 29 March 1995) is a Haitian professional [[association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[forward (association football)|forward]] for [[Süper Lig]] club [[Çaykur Rizespor]], on loan from [[AEK Athens F.C.|AEK Athens]], and the [[Haiti national football team|Haiti national team]].

==Club career==
===College and amateur===
Pierrot played two years of [[College soccer in the United States|college soccer]] at [[Northeastern University]] between 2014 and 2015,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.gonu.com/roster.aspx?rp_id=3064|title=Frantzdy Pierrot - 2014 Men's Soccer - Northeastern University Athletics|website=www.gonu.com|access-date=29 July 2018|archive-date=29 July 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180729230455/http://www.gonu.com/roster.aspx?rp_id=3064|url-status=live}}</ref> before transferring to [[Coastal Carolina University]] in 2016, where he played for another two years.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://goccusports.com/roster.aspx?rp_id=2106|title=Coastal Carolina Official Athletics Website|website=goccusports.com|access-date=29 July 2018|archive-date=29 July 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180729200648/https://goccusports.com/roster.aspx?rp_id=2106|url-status=live}}</ref>

Pierrot also appeared for [[USL PDL]] side [[Reading United AC|Reading United]] in 2016<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.uslpdl.com/roster_players/12301722|title=Reading United AC - 2016 Regular Season - Roster - # - Frantzdy Pierrot - F|website=www.uslpdl.com|access-date=29 July 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160524005543/http://www.uslpdl.com/roster_players/12301722|archive-date=24 May 2016|url-status=dead}}</ref> and 2017.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.uslpdl.com/roster_players/18320217|title=Reading United AC - 2017 Regular Season - Roster - #11 - Frantzdy Pierrot - F|website=www.uslpdl.com|access-date=29 July 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180729230406/https://www.uslpdl.com/roster_players/18320217|archive-date=29 July 2018|url-status=dead}}</ref>

===Professional===
On 19 January 2018, Pierrot was selected with the 27th overall pick of the [[2018 MLS SuperDraft]] by [[Colorado Rapids]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.denverpost.com/2018/01/19/colorado-rapids-mls-superdraft/|title=Colorado Rapids select pair of forwards in MLS SuperDraft second round|date=19 January 2018|access-date=29 July 2018|archive-date=13 June 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200613234510/https://www.denverpost.com/2018/01/19/colorado-rapids-mls-superdraft/|url-status=live}}</ref> However, he did not sign with the club.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.burgundywave.com/2018/1/31/16957800/frantzdy-pierrot-and-brian-iloski-leave-the-colorado-rapids-for-europe|title=Frantzdy Pierrot and Brian Iloski leave the Rapids for Europe|access-date=29 July 2018|archive-date=20 February 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180220152106/https://www.burgundywave.com/2018/1/31/16957800/frantzdy-pierrot-and-brian-iloski-leave-the-colorado-rapids-for-europe|url-status=live}}</ref>

On 27 July 2018, Pierrot signed a four-year contract with [[Belgian First Division A]] side [[Royal Excel Mouscron|Mouscron]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.dhnet.be/sports/football/division-1a/mouscron/l-haitien-frantzdy-pierrot-signe-pour-4-ans-a-mouscron-5b5b060655324d3f13994569|title=L'Haïtien Frantzdy Pierrot signe pour 4 ans à Mouscron|last=DH.be|access-date=29 July 2018|archive-date=29 July 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180729230400/http://www.dhnet.be/sports/football/division-1a/mouscron/l-haitien-frantzdy-pierrot-signe-pour-4-ans-a-mouscron-5b5b060655324d3f13994569|url-status=live}}</ref> One year later, he joined French [[Ligue 2]] club [[En Avant Guingamp|Guingamp]]. He signed a four-year contract.<ref>[https://www.eaguingamp.com/frantzdy-pierrot-sengage-4-ans/ FRANTZDY PIERROT S’ENGAGE 4 ANS] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190823100143/https://www.eaguingamp.com/frantzdy-pierrot-sengage-4-ans/ |date=23 August 2019 }}, eaguingamp.com, 22 August 2019</ref>

On 3 July 2022, Pierrot signed a three-year contract with [[Maccabi Haifa F.C.|Maccabi Haifa]] of the [[Israeli Premier League]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.haititempo.com/foot-transfert-officiel-frantzdy-pierrot-signe-au-maccabi-haifa/|title=Foot- Transfert: Officiel, Frantzdy Pierrot signe au Maccabi Haïfa|date=1 July 2022|first=Gary|last=Eliézer|access-date=17 August 2022|archive-date=18 August 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220818190913/https://www.haititempo.com/foot-transfert-officiel-frantzdy-pierrot-signe-au-maccabi-haifa/|url-status=live}}</ref>

On 10 September 2024, Pierrot signed a three-year contract with [[AEK Athens F.C.|AEK Athens]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.aekfc.gr/newsdetails/stin-aek-o-franzi-piero-131832.htm?lang=en&path=-533260310|title=Frantzdy Pierrot joins AEK FC!|website=www.aekfc.gr}}</ref>

==International career==
Pierrot was called up to the 40-man provisional squad for the [[2019 CONCACAF Gold Cup]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.facebook.com/fhfhaiti/posts/10156227801021188|title=LISTE DES JOUEURS PRÉ-SÉLECTIONNÉS|publisher=FHF Facebook|date=16 May 2019|language=haitian creole}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://haititempo.com/gold-cup-2019-une-pre-liste-de-40-grenadiers-devoilee/|title=Gold Cup 2019 : Une pré-liste de 40 Grenadiers dévoilée|trans-title=Gold Cup 2019: A pre-list of 40 Grenadiers unveiled|newspaper=[[Haiti Tempo]]|date=17 May 2019|language=fr}}</ref> He was included in the final squad.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.facebook.com/fhfhaiti/posts/10156242632146188|title=LES 23 CONVOQUÉS|publisher=FHF Facebook|date=23 May 2019|language=haitian creole}}</ref>

Pierrot was called up to the 35-man provisional squad for the [[2023 CONCACAF Gold Cup]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.infohaiti.net/gold-cup-2023-une-preliste-de-35-joueurs-convoques/|title=Gold Cup 2023 : Une préliste de 35 joueurs convoqués|trans-title=Gold Cup 2023 : A pre list of 35 players called-up|publisher=Info Haiti|location=Port-au-Prince|website=www.infohaiti.net|last=Bordes|first=Gérald|date=25 May 2023|access-date=7 June 2023|language=fr}}</ref> He was also included in the reduced 28 player squad.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.infohaiti.net/une-nouvelle-preliste-de-28-joueurs-pour-debuter-le-camp-de-preparation/#:~:text=Port%2Dau%2DPrince%20%E2%80%93%20Par,%C3%A9dition%20de%20la%20Gold%20Cup.|title=Une nouvelle préliste de 28 joueurs pour débuter le camp de préparation|trans-title=A new pre list of 28 players to start the preparation camp|publisher=Info Haiti|location=Port-au-Prince|website=www.infohaiti.net|last=Bordes|first=Gérald|date=3 June 2023|access-date=7 June 2023|language=fr}}</ref> Pierrot was included in the final squad.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.facebook.com/fhfhaiti/posts/pfbid02twWi2Yh9pncra1iNhc9uTeZjXRCZBczd4Lo8ramvSteUtvyc39mxELKLwLxbEyBCl|title=Le sélectionneur national, Gabriel Pellegrino Calderon, a dévoilé ce lundi 19 juin dans la matinée, la liste officielle des grenadiers retenus pour la Gold Cup 2023|publisher=Haitian Football Federation|date=19 June 2023|access-date=19 June 2023|language=fr|via=Facebook}}</ref>

==Personal life==
Pierrot was born in [[Haiti]], but grew up in [[Massachusetts]] in the United States where he attended [[Melrose High School (Massachusetts)|Melrose High School]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.espn.com/blog/boston/high-school/post/_/id/28543/melroses-frantzdy-pierrot-out-for-the-season|title=Melrose's Frantzdy Pierrot out for the season|website=ESPN|date=5 December 2013|access-date=29 July 2018|archive-date=29 July 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180729230511/http://www.espn.com/blog/boston/high-school/post/_/id/28543/melroses-frantzdy-pierrot-out-for-the-season|url-status=live}}</ref> His younger brother [[Frantz Pierrot]] is also a professional footballer.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://lookcharms.com/foot-transfer-frantzdy-pierrots-little-brother-drafted-in-mls/|title=Foot-Transfer: Frantzdy Pierrot's little brother drafted in MLS!|date=22 December 2022|access-date=13 August 2023|archive-date=13 August 2023|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230813160802/https://lookcharms.com/foot-transfer-frantzdy-pierrots-little-brother-drafted-in-mls/|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://int.soccerway.com/players/frantz-pierrot/500828/|title=Haiti - F. Pierrot - Profile with news, career statistics and history - Soccerway|website=int.soccerway.com|access-date=13 August 2023|archive-date=13 August 2023|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230813160801/https://int.soccerway.com/players/frantz-pierrot/500828/|url-status=live}}</ref> Pierrot is an American citizen.<ref>{{cite web | url=https://www.wildeslaw.com/immigration-resources/latest-immigration-news/how-we-helped-maccabi-haifas-frantzdy-pierrot-in-israel/ | title=How we helped Maccabi Haifa's Frantzdy Pierrot in Israel | date=12 October 2023 }}</ref>

